<subSubSection pageId="3" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,1416,1674]" pageId="3">
There is a published list of the flowering plants in the area where the 
<typeStatus box="[1086,1136,1416,1442]" pageId="3">type</typeStatus>
specimen was collected (
<bibRefCitation author="Amorim, A. M. &amp; Jardim, J. G. &amp; Lopes, M. M. M. &amp; Fiaschi, P. &amp; Borges, R. A. X. &amp; Perdiz, R. O. &amp; Thomas, W. W." box="[159,410,1454,1480]" pageId="3" pagination="313 - 348" refId="ref1842" refString="Amorim, A. M., Jardim, J. G., Lopes, M. M. M., Fiaschi, P., Borges, R. A. X., Perdiz, R. O. &amp; Thomas, W. W. (2009) Angiospermas em remanescentes de floresta montana no sul da Bahia, Brasil. Biota Neotropica 9: 313 - 348." type="journal article" year="2009">
Amorim 
<emphasis box="[272,334,1454,1479]" italics="true" pageId="3">et al.</emphasis>
2009
</bibRefCitation>
). In this list only two 
<taxonomicName box="[683,789,1454,1479]" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Encyclia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="3" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[683,789,1454,1479]" italics="true" pageId="3">Encyclia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
were reported and not identified to species level, as 
<taxonomicName box="[151,315,1493,1519]" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Encyclia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="3" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="undefined-1">
<emphasis box="[151,254,1493,1518]" italics="true" pageId="3">Encyclia</emphasis>
sp. 1
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[372,539,1493,1519]" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Encyclia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="3" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="undefined-2">
<emphasis box="[372,474,1493,1518]" italics="true" pageId="3">Encyclia</emphasis>
sp. 2
</taxonomicName>
. The latter corresponds to 
<taxonomicName box="[850,991,1493,1518]" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Encyclia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="3" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="fimbriata">
<emphasis box="[850,991,1493,1518]" italics="true" pageId="3">E. fimbriata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, here described, whereas 
<taxonomicName class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Encyclia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="3" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="undefined-1">
<emphasis box="[1293,1396,1493,1518]" italics="true" pageId="3">Encyclia</emphasis>
sp. 1
</taxonomicName>
is in fact a specimen of 
<taxonomicName authority="Fowlie (1991: 26)" authorityName="Fowlie" authorityPageNumber="26" authorityYear="1991" box="[448,802,1531,1557]" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Encyclia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="3" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="unaensis">
<emphasis box="[448,582,1532,1557]" italics="true" pageId="3">E. unaensis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Fowlie, J. A." box="[589,802,1531,1557]" pageId="3" pagination="26 - 27" refId="ref2449" refString="Fowlie, J. A. (1991) A new Encyclia species from the floodplains of Una (Bahia), Encyclia unaensis Fowl., sp. nov. Orchid Digest 55: 26 - 27." type="journal article" year="1991">Fowlie (1991: 26)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, vegetatively much smaller than 
<taxonomicName box="[1187,1328,1532,1557]" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Encyclia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="3" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="fimbriata">
<emphasis box="[1187,1328,1532,1557]" italics="true" pageId="3">E. fimbriata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and with completely different flowers. The measurements in our description above are based on the single specimen available to us, but we have bracketed these data a little so that the description is more likely to apply to additional collections, if they are ever made.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
